{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01XYWZG3AAwzRYhnfjZTnMT4","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# address-book-quarkus\n     2→\n     3→This project uses Quarkus, the Supersonic Subatomic Java Framework.\n     4→\n     5→If you want to learn more about Quarkus, please visit its website: <https://quarkus.io/>.\n     6→\n     7→## Running the application in dev mode\n     8→\n     9→You can run your application in dev mode that enables live coding using:\n    10→\n    11→```shell script\n    12→./mvnw quarkus:dev\n    13→```\n    14→\n    15→> **_NOTE:_**  Quarkus now ships with a Dev UI, which is available in dev mode only at <http://localhost:8080/q/dev/>.\n    16→\n    17→## Packaging and running the application\n    18→\n    19→The application can be packaged using:\n    20→\n    21→```shell script\n    22→./mvnw package\n    23→```\n    24→\n    25→It produces the `quarkus-run.jar` file in the `target/quarkus-app/` directory.\n    26→Be aware that it’s not an _über-jar_ as the dependencies are copied into the `target/quarkus-app/lib/` directory.\n    27→\n    28→The application is now runnable using `java -jar target/quarkus-app/quarkus-run.jar`.\n    29→\n    30→If you want to build an _über-jar_, execute the following command:\n    31→\n    32→```shell script\n    33→./mvnw package -Dquarkus.package.jar.type=uber-jar\n    34→```\n    35→\n    36→The application, packaged as an _über-jar_, is now runnable using `java -jar target/*-runner.jar`.\n    37→\n    38→## Creating a native executable\n    39→\n    40→You can create a native executable using:\n    41→\n    42→```shell script\n    43→./mvnw package -Dnative\n    44→```\n    45→\n    46→Or, if you don't have GraalVM installed, you can run the native executable build in a container using:\n    47→\n    48→```shell script\n    49→./mvnw package -Dnative -Dquarkus.native.container-build=true\n    50→```\n    51→\n    52→You can then execute your native executable with: `./target/address-book-quarkus-1.0.0-SNAPSHOT-runner`\n    53→\n    54→If you want to learn more about building native executables, please consult <https://quarkus.io/guides/maven-tooling>.\n    55→\n    56→## Provided Code\n    57→\n    58→### REST\n    59→\n    60→Easily start your REST Web Services\n    61→\n    62→[Related guide section...](https://quarkus.io/guides/getting-started-reactive#reactive-jax-rs-resources)\n    63→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_017Amhz943wFoY7E1c27x66R","session_id":"65247950-fc0a-4cbd-9aef-1138c7766d91","uuid":"5869543a-b5e5-49ba-ba16-e2b95dc5355a"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_017Amhz943wFoY7E1c27x66R","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Summary of the project:\n\nThis is a Quarkus-based Address Book web application using Jakarta EE (formerly Java EE) technologies. Key characteristics:\n\n1. Project Structure:\n- Maven-based project\n- Quarkus framework\n- Jakarta JSF (JavaServer Faces) for web interface\n- Hibernate ORM for persistence\n- H2 in-memory database\n\n2. Main Components:\n- Contact Entity: Represents contact information (name, email, phone, birthday)\n- ContactController: Manages CRUD operations and pagination\n- ContactFacade: Data access layer using generic AbstractFacade\n- JSF-based web interface with CRUD operations\n\n3. Key Configuration:\n- Uses Quarkus 3.30.5\n- Java 17\n- H2 in-memory database\n- Development mode with live coding support\n- Supports native executable compilation\n\n4. Notable Features:\n- Pagination support\n- Localized messages (Bundle.properties)\n- Validation messages\n- JSF-based web interface\n- REST support\n\n5. Deployment Options:\n- Dev mode: `./mvnw quarkus:dev`\n- JAR packaging: `./mvnw package`\n- Native executable: `./mvnw package -Dnative`\n\nDeployment will typically run on `http://localhost:8080`, with a web interface for managing contact information.\n\nThe code is licensed under the Eclipse Distribution License v1.0, which allows for free use and distribution.\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any specific aspect of the project?"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"65247950-fc0a-4cbd-9aef-1138c7766d91","uuid":"2ffc34f6-7904-4471-b351-4a1d5bee36a1"}
